1
00:00:02,159 --> 00:00:05,458
<i>[ Disco, Woman Vocalizing ]</i>

2
00:00:05,563 --> 00:00:09,363
[ Lorne ] Uh-huh.
Oh, I promise you. It'll be fabulous.

3
00:00:09,467 --> 00:00:11,662
Believe me,Jerry. Yes.

4
00:00:11,769 --> 00:00:14,761
It's <i>Grapes of Wrath</i>
in outer space. Uh-huh.

5
00:00:14,872 --> 00:00:17,932
Oh, it's got heart.
Yes, it's got laser battles.

6
00:00:18,042 --> 00:00:21,443
It's got a timely message
of interstellar poverty.

7
00:00:21,545 --> 00:00:25,538
Uh-huh. Listen, have your assistant
call my assistant.

8
00:00:25,649 --> 00:00:27,947
We'll set somethin' up.
Good enough.

9
00:00:28,052 --> 00:00:32,079
J.C., listen,
just got off the Nextel with Big B.

10
00:00:32,189 --> 00:00:35,158
Yeah, intrigued, but wants to know
who's playing Tom Joad. Uh-huh.

11
00:00:35,259 --> 00:00:38,558
Well, I'm pretty sure that
Henry Fonda's dead, sweetie.

12
00:00:38,662 --> 00:00:40,562
Yeah. ''Bring him back to life''?

13
00:00:40,664 --> 00:00:43,326
Let me talk to my science people.
Okay, no promises.

14
00:00:43,434 --> 00:00:46,232
- Directors. Harmonica!
- Lorney Tunes!

15
00:00:46,337 --> 00:00:49,238
Oh, the eyes, the hair, the dress.

16
00:00:49,340 --> 00:00:51,274
It's no wonder the fourth floor
has a crush on you.

17
00:00:51,375 --> 00:00:53,570
Hey, tell me, priceless.
Where do I find Angel?

18
00:00:53,677 --> 00:00:56,407
Just called. He's on his way back in
from a field mission.

19
00:00:56,514 --> 00:00:59,449
<i>Though I wouldn't, if I were you.</i>
<i>It sounds like he's in a mood.</i>

20
00:00:59,550 --> 00:01:02,747
Oh, don't worry, darlin'. I've pulled
the big boy out of many a broodfest.

21
00:01:02,853 --> 00:01:04,844
- It shouldn't be that--
<i>- [ Squishy Footsteps ]</i>

22
00:01:06,757 --> 00:01:08,816
Ew.

23
00:01:08,926 --> 00:01:11,417
Angel, how did the new
neural-intercept grenade work?

24
00:01:11,529 --> 00:01:14,157
It didn't.

25
00:01:14,265 --> 00:01:16,631
Right. I'll take it down to Fred,
have her look at it.

26
00:01:16,734 --> 00:01:18,634
Hey, Angelheart.
Wes, if you see Fred...

27
00:01:18,736 --> 00:01:20,636
can you have her
pencil me in for later?

28
00:01:20,738 --> 00:01:23,332
I've gotta talk to her about
Henry Fonda's big comeback.

29
00:01:23,441 --> 00:01:25,932
- [ Wesley ] All right.
- Angel, we gotta have a confab.

30
00:01:26,043 --> 00:01:28,876
<i>- Es muy importante.</i>
- Lorne--

31
00:01:28,979 --> 00:01:32,107
It's about the party. I've done
all I can do for the big to-do...

32
00:01:32,216 --> 00:01:35,344
but we've still got a few bugs
to comb out of the cootie garage.

33
00:01:35,453 --> 00:01:37,944
A bridge too far?
Let me try it again.

34
00:01:38,055 --> 00:01:40,751
Lorne, I've been out all night.
I'm beat up. I'm exhausted.

35
00:01:40,858 --> 00:01:43,827
I'm covered head to toe in Thraxis blood,
which actually kind of burns...

36
00:01:43,928 --> 00:01:46,123
so this is all gonna have to wait
until I take a shower.

37
00:01:46,230 --> 00:01:48,061
- You killed a Thraxis? But--
- Shower.

38
00:01:49,633 --> 00:01:53,433
Van, why don't we scratch the Thraxis
off of the invite list?

39
00:01:53,537 --> 00:01:56,005
And you got a copy of that print ad
we're gonna run this week?

40
00:01:56,106 --> 00:01:58,472
- Yeah. Right.
- What is this?

41
00:01:58,576 --> 00:02:01,010
''Wolfram and Hart
wants to be up your alley''?

42
00:02:01,111 --> 00:02:03,272
That's like a bus station
pickup line. Change it.

43
00:02:03,380 --> 00:02:05,644
On second thought, burn it.
Grab yourself a bagel or somethin' too.

44
00:02:05,749 --> 00:02:07,979
You look a little waxy.

45
00:02:09,119 --> 00:02:11,087
[ Sighs ]

46
00:02:14,925 --> 00:02:16,893
[ Sighs ]

47
00:02:30,708 --> 00:02:33,108
Ooh, ouch.

48
00:02:33,210 --> 00:02:36,737
That's an adult-size bangaroo. Hello!

49
00:02:36,847 --> 00:02:40,010
- [ Groaning ]
<i>- Oh, Mr. Smiles?</i>

50
00:02:40,117 --> 00:02:42,381
Oh, come on.
You can't ignore me forever.

51
00:02:42,486 --> 00:02:45,182
- [ Sighs ]
- Well, fine.

52
00:02:45,289 --> 00:02:47,723
Looks like you're gonna have to
slap a Band Aid on that melon...

53
00:02:47,825 --> 00:02:51,192
<i>and draw a grin on that bewitching</i>
<i>green mug and go right back out there.</i>

54
00:02:51,295 --> 00:02:53,092
On the count of nine, sunshine.

55
00:02:53,197 --> 00:02:57,463
One, two, three--

56
00:02:57,568 --> 00:03:00,093
The show stops for no demon, Lorne.

57
00:03:00,204 --> 00:03:03,367
Four, five--
They're all waiting for you.

58
00:03:03,474 --> 00:03:05,203
<i>Six, seven--</i>

59
00:03:05,309 --> 00:03:07,937
They're counting on you.
Eight-- Comin' up on nine.

60
00:03:08,045 --> 00:03:11,913
<i>They're gonna eat you up</i>
<i>with a spoon because you're so...</i>

61
00:03:12,016 --> 00:03:14,280
<i>- scrumptious.!</i>
- Shut up!

62
00:03:24,395 --> 00:03:26,363
[ Sighs ]

63
00:04:43,941 --> 00:04:46,910
<i>[ Shower Running ]</i>

64
00:04:49,213 --> 00:04:51,181
<i>[ Shower Stops ]</i>

65
00:04:53,117 --> 00:04:55,142
<i>[ Eve ]</i>
<i>Hi.</i>

66
00:05:00,891 --> 00:05:04,327
The door was open.
Well, unlocked.

67
00:05:05,963 --> 00:05:08,261
Well, I had a key.

68
00:05:16,607 --> 00:05:19,508
<i>- [ Key Clatters ]</i>
<i>- So, uh, wow.</i>

69
00:05:19,610 --> 00:05:22,670
You take a long shower for a guy.

70
00:05:22,780 --> 00:05:24,714
Were we having some
gentleman's time?

71
00:05:24,815 --> 00:05:27,045
- ''Gentleman's''?
<i>- I mean, I understand.</i>

72
00:05:27,151 --> 00:05:29,517
You're running the whole circus now,
a lot of pressure.

73
00:05:29,620 --> 00:05:33,181
Especially with your hands-on policy.
No pun intended.

74
00:05:34,491 --> 00:05:37,016
I'm sure you could use a release.

75
00:05:37,127 --> 00:05:39,755
No releasing,just bathing.
That's what one does...

76
00:05:39,863 --> 00:05:44,391
<i>after bashing open a demonic pinata</i>
<i>full of rancid Tabasco.</i>

77
00:05:44,501 --> 00:05:47,368
- What do you want, Eve?
- You stood me up.

78
00:05:47,471 --> 00:05:50,963
<i>We had a 7:30, Angel.</i>
<i>A meeting.</i>

79
00:05:51,075 --> 00:05:55,409
- Oh, right. Uh, I'll get my pants.
<i>- [ Elevator Bell Dings ]</i>

80
00:05:57,047 --> 00:06:00,107
- So how's it going, Angel?
- [ Sighs ]

81
00:06:00,217 --> 00:06:02,981
I don't know how
to answer that question.

82
00:06:04,188 --> 00:06:07,715
I don't know. Good. Bad.

83
00:06:07,825 --> 00:06:10,817
I spent years doing everything
I could to bring this company down.

84
00:06:10,928 --> 00:06:13,522
Now I'm the C.E.O., and I have to
question every move I make...

85
00:06:13,630 --> 00:06:16,599
because any one of them could be
exactly what the senior partners want.

86
00:06:16,700 --> 00:06:18,930
So, no, I have no idea how it's goin'.

87
00:06:19,036 --> 00:06:22,233
Hey, at least you can still get
your nocturnal jollies...

88
00:06:22,339 --> 00:06:24,967
saving the downtrodden
from things that go bump in the night.

89
00:06:25,075 --> 00:06:27,441
You said it yourself--
''Everyone needs a release.''

90
00:06:27,544 --> 00:06:29,739
No, I said you need a release.

91
00:06:29,847 --> 00:06:31,747
Not everyone bottles
all this stuff up like you.

92
00:06:31,849 --> 00:06:33,976
- I don't bottle.
- You bottle.

93
00:06:34,084 --> 00:06:35,813
- I don't bottle.
<i>- [ Bell Dings ]</i>

94
00:06:36,854 --> 00:06:39,118
[ Groaning ]

95
00:06:42,760 --> 00:06:44,751
Why does it look like
we're havin' a party in here?

96
00:06:44,862 --> 00:06:46,762
Maybe 'cause we're
havin' a party in here.

97
00:06:46,864 --> 00:06:48,991
The Wolfram and Hart Halloween bash?

98
00:06:49,099 --> 00:06:51,659
<i>Ring a bell? Biggest event</i>
<i>on the company calendar?</i>

99
00:06:51,769 --> 00:06:54,203
I sent you a small
forest's worth of memos on it.

100
00:06:54,304 --> 00:06:57,364
- We're havin' it here?
- You see what I'm up against?

101
00:06:57,474 --> 00:07:00,170
That's what our 7:30 was about, Angel--
your party.

102
00:07:00,277 --> 00:07:04,213
- My party?
- Yeah, listen, here's the snafu in a nutshell, top cat.

103
00:07:04,314 --> 00:07:06,441
Uh, nobody's comin'.

104
00:07:07,951 --> 00:07:11,318
Well, some people are comin',
but the right people--

105
00:07:11,421 --> 00:07:13,787
the A-list people--
they seem to be giving it a miss.

106
00:07:13,891 --> 00:07:16,451
- And if they don't show up,
this shindig is gonna be a bust.
- Good.

107
00:07:16,560 --> 00:07:19,120
- Good?
- Yeah, I wasn't too crazy
about this thing to begin with.

108
00:07:19,229 --> 00:07:21,390
I mean, we are talking about
our clients, right?

109
00:07:21,498 --> 00:07:24,160
Our evil clients. Not the sort of folks
I'd really like to show a good time.

110
00:07:24,268 --> 00:07:27,704
I'd be a lot happier if the whole thing
just kind of fell through.

111
00:07:27,805 --> 00:07:30,365
- Then we can get back to--
- [ Laughs ] Okay! Okay, you're killin' me!

112
00:07:30,474 --> 00:07:33,068
Can't you just feel up
the big picture, Mr. Magoo?

113
00:07:33,177 --> 00:07:35,509
It's not about good and evil.
It's about party.

114
00:07:35,612 --> 00:07:38,479
Party! Capital P,
rhymes with me.

115
00:07:38,582 --> 00:07:41,176
I'm about to have a stroke here,
'cause you're killin' me!

116
00:07:43,253 --> 00:07:48,190
Listen, I can see that
you're in a state...

117
00:07:48,292 --> 00:07:52,251
a mood, a snit, even.

118
00:07:52,362 --> 00:07:56,924
So what say we talk about this once
you've calmed down a bit?

119
00:08:01,205 --> 00:08:03,070
Yeah, sure. That's fine with--

120
00:08:03,173 --> 00:08:05,801
Great. Your office, 25 minutes.

121
00:08:10,681 --> 00:08:13,081
- Was Angel mad?
- Shouldn't he be?

122
00:08:13,183 --> 00:08:15,174
We sent him out there with
a defective piece of weaponry.

123
00:08:15,285 --> 00:08:17,753
Which ''we'' are we talking about?

124
00:08:17,855 --> 00:08:22,087
Fred, these techno-mystical hybrids
are a complicated affair.

125
00:08:22,192 --> 00:08:24,752
I don't know.
They seem kind of simple to me.

126
00:08:24,862 --> 00:08:28,730
<i>It's just a little handheld,</i>
<i>spell-casting robot, right?</i>

127
00:08:28,832 --> 00:08:32,268
So it's either the robot or the spell
that we have a problem with.

128
00:08:32,369 --> 00:08:35,395
Well, the grenade's core
enchantment looks operational...

129
00:08:35,505 --> 00:08:38,099
so I think we're talking about
a faulty trigger mechanism.

130
00:08:38,208 --> 00:08:40,642
No. Wait a minute.
I designed that mechanism myself.

131
00:08:40,744 --> 00:08:43,042
<i>Yeah, that's right, and I machined it.</i>

132
00:08:43,146 --> 00:08:46,809
It was beautiful work
on both counts, if I may say.

133
00:08:46,917 --> 00:08:49,681
- You may.
- [ Chuckles ]

134
00:08:49,786 --> 00:08:51,981
I agree, as a sculptural piece.

135
00:08:52,089 --> 00:08:54,250
But the device's trigger
may not have been refined enough...

136
00:08:54,358 --> 00:08:56,258
to actually trigger the effect.

137
00:08:56,360 --> 00:08:58,260
Happy Halloween, kids.

138
00:08:58,362 --> 00:09:01,092
<i>How do you know your spell-casters</i>
<i>didn't screw up the payload?</i>

139
00:09:01,198 --> 00:09:04,998
Because I went over the work,
and I got that knowing feeling
you get when you know something.

140
00:09:05,102 --> 00:09:08,230
- Trick or treat?
- Hi, Lorne.
- Hi.

141
00:09:08,338 --> 00:09:10,898
What do you say we put away your
little sci-fi toys for a little bit, huh?

142
00:09:11,008 --> 00:09:13,602
Maybe we could talk about
something a little more important...

143
00:09:13,710 --> 00:09:16,178
like my monster mash.

144
00:09:16,280 --> 00:09:18,510
Oh, yeah, your party.

145
00:09:18,615 --> 00:09:21,675
<i>Our</i> party, Tweety Bird, which,
by the way, is dying on the vine.

146
00:09:21,785 --> 00:09:25,277
I could really, really, really use
some help from you guys. Some backup.

147
00:09:25,389 --> 00:09:28,517
I wasn't really planning on going.

148
00:09:30,360 --> 00:09:33,158
Wes, do you hear this crazy talk?

149
00:09:33,263 --> 00:09:37,097
Uh, well, I really hadn't given
much thought to going myself.

150
00:09:38,402 --> 00:09:40,302
<i>Et tu,</i> Brutuses?

151
00:09:40,404 --> 00:09:43,669
Why is it so hard to get anyone
to have any fun around here?

152
00:09:43,774 --> 00:09:45,901
<i>[ Knox ]</i>
<i>You should go.</i>

153
00:09:46,009 --> 00:09:49,206
It's the Halloween blowout
to end all blowouts.

154
00:09:49,313 --> 00:09:51,338
Last year, uh,
[ Chuckling ]

155
00:09:51,448 --> 00:09:53,939
<i>they took a bunch of cows...</i>

156
00:09:54,051 --> 00:09:56,781
and put them in this
giant wicker effigy of Krishna...

157
00:09:56,887 --> 00:09:58,855
doused it with Sambuca and--

158
00:10:01,625 --> 00:10:06,085
Uh, well, anyway,
it's a hell of a good time.

159
00:10:07,965 --> 00:10:11,128
I really wanna get this operational
before Angel goes out again.

160
00:10:11,234 --> 00:10:13,634
- Yes, I'll stay too.
- Wha--

161
00:10:13,737 --> 00:10:16,729
- I'm sure we can work it out together.
- No.

162
00:10:16,840 --> 00:10:21,641
No, no, no, no, no, no, no! Wes, Fred,
you're coming. Look at yourselves.

163
00:10:21,745 --> 00:10:24,077
You're wound tighter
than Martha Stewart's watch.

164
00:10:24,181 --> 00:10:29,050
Isn't there anyone else who could fix
the little boo-boos on this thing?

165
00:10:30,320 --> 00:10:32,220
<i>[ Knox ]</i>
<i>I can do that.</i>

166
00:10:32,322 --> 00:10:35,587
It's probably the trigger
mechanism anyway.

167
00:10:35,692 --> 00:10:38,661
Great. Problem solved.

168
00:10:38,762 --> 00:10:41,993
I'll see you two in Angel's office,
1 5 minutes.

169
00:10:43,967 --> 00:10:45,696
<i>[ Knocking On Door ]</i>

170
00:10:46,803 --> 00:10:48,566
- Hey, Lorne.
- Hey, hey.

171
00:10:48,672 --> 00:10:52,199
Uh, sorry to interrupt.
Not to be a pest...

172
00:10:52,309 --> 00:10:54,743
but I just wanted to go over
a little stratego, amigo.

173
00:10:54,845 --> 00:10:57,780
- Sorry?
- Um, you're my big gun, Gunn.

174
00:10:57,881 --> 00:10:59,712
<i>Ace in hole.</i>
<i>Ball in pocket.</i>

175
00:10:59,816 --> 00:11:01,784
You're the key on my kite string.

176
00:11:01,885 --> 00:11:03,580
Okay.

177
00:11:03,687 --> 00:11:06,679
We gotta turn Angel around
on this whole party idea.

178
00:11:06,790 --> 00:11:09,725
- We do?
- I know he's the boss and everything...

179
00:11:09,826 --> 00:11:13,091
<i>but you're up and coming here, and it's time</i>
<i>for you to spread your wings, legal eagle.</i>

180
00:11:13,196 --> 00:11:16,029
From now on, I want you
to stake out your territory...

181
00:11:16,133 --> 00:11:17,930
and I want you to keep it staked.

182
00:11:18,035 --> 00:11:20,435
Stake. Territory. Sure.

183
00:11:20,537 --> 00:11:23,973
Lorne, I'm a little busy right now.
I have a deposition to get ready for.

184
00:11:24,074 --> 00:11:26,542
- But I will definitely get to that.
- Great.

185
00:11:26,643 --> 00:11:30,704
Just what I wanted to hear.
Angel's office, 1 0 minutes.

186
00:11:30,814 --> 00:11:33,214
<i>[ Door Closes ]</i>

187
00:11:40,424 --> 00:11:42,949
In my day, no self-respecting
creature of the night...

188
00:11:43,060 --> 00:11:45,551
went out on All Hallow's Eve.

189
00:11:45,662 --> 00:11:49,894
<i>We left that to the poseurs-- the blighters</i>
<i>who had to dress up and try to be scary.</i>

190
00:11:52,602 --> 00:11:56,003
Magic windows.
Will the perks never end?

191
00:11:56,106 --> 00:11:57,971
[ Italian ]

192
00:12:00,110 --> 00:12:02,078
Ciao.

193
00:12:02,179 --> 00:12:04,409
- What'd I miss?
- Us waiting.

194
00:12:04,514 --> 00:12:07,312
Oh, right. Sorry.

195
00:12:07,417 --> 00:12:10,113
So, uh, Angel, we just wanted
to take a moment...

196
00:12:10,220 --> 00:12:14,247
and emphasize how important
this party really is to us.

197
00:12:14,357 --> 00:12:15,984
I gotta say Lorne is right.

198
00:12:16,093 --> 00:12:18,789
We gotta show all the big-bads
that the new regime is here to stay...

199
00:12:18,895 --> 00:12:21,455
<i>which, for the most part,</i>
<i>boils down to image.</i>

200
00:12:21,565 --> 00:12:23,795
And image-wise, if this party
doesn't kick ass, we lose face.

201
00:12:23,900 --> 00:12:25,800
And believe me, Milk Dud,
speaking as the head...

202
00:12:25,902 --> 00:12:28,598
of your P.R. department,
we need all the face we can get.

203
00:12:28,705 --> 00:12:31,139
- ''Milk Dud''?
- Said with affection.

204
00:12:31,241 --> 00:12:33,971
Okay, listen, I understand the whole
keeping-up-appearances concept...

205
00:12:34,077 --> 00:12:37,376
but everyone comin' to this thing
is unrepentant, dyed-in-the-wool evil.

206
00:12:37,481 --> 00:12:39,949
Angel, a good host just doesn't
make these sort of judgments.

207
00:12:40,050 --> 00:12:43,611
We don't know how many of them are holdin'
grudges against us or against each other.

208
00:12:43,720 --> 00:12:46,621
<i>It's a perfect recipe for</i>
<i>an out-of-control bloodbath.</i>

209
00:12:46,723 --> 00:12:49,351
That's describing every good party
I've ever been to. [ Laughs ]

210
00:12:51,628 --> 00:12:55,120
Listen, Angel, don't worry about a thing.
This is my forte.

211
00:12:55,232 --> 00:12:58,395
<i>I ran Caritas for years--</i>
<i>a nightclub with an open-door policy.</i>

212
00:12:58,502 --> 00:13:00,402
The good, the bad,
the hideously ugly--

213
00:13:00,504 --> 00:13:02,404
They all bellied up to my demon bar...

214
00:13:02,506 --> 00:13:05,475
but they all played nicely
together while they were there.

215
00:13:05,575 --> 00:13:08,408
This is exactly the kind of ethical
tightrope you've got to walk now.

216
00:13:08,512 --> 00:13:11,345
<i>Which brings up another point--</i>
<i>your employees.</i>

217
00:13:11,448 --> 00:13:15,475
